    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-quality specimen of the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. It features a meticulously maintained vacuum system and a robust Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the power delivery remains as linear and responsive as the day it left Hiroshima. The chassis dynamics are preserved by its original lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a perfect 50:50 weight distribution. With a recent compression test confirming the integrity of the apex seals and a flawless factory finish, this FD represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
      "price": 48500.0,
